				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NEW Solo Methods<a name="72132"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 17 05 5:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Now I know this is meant to be a thread about soloing, but I was just thinking about the AE nerf.  Bard AE's now only hit stationary targets practically in melee range. So a new problem becomes how to get the mobs to stand still.
<br />

<br />
Root...no thats just as bad as standing there. 
<br />

<br />
Thats all the solo options I came up with but here are a few duo options:
<br />

<br />
A tank...no that means they are getting hit and will need a healer.
<br />

<br />
Another bard...no they have the same problem as we do...
<br />

<br />
An enchanter... Yes! This is the winner. Enchanters get a nice line of spells that solves all the problems mentioned above...they get a set of AE stuns. The mobs are standing still, not hitting anyone. And the stuns cost very little mana wise (Such that we could assist in mana regen between fights easily)
<br />

<br />
Now there are a few flaws to the plan...lots of new mobs cant be stunned with those spells, if the chanter lags for a bit he is liable to wind up dead, and your limited by the enchanters mana bar. 
<br />

<br />
But then again you are no longer ae soloing. I was just looking for a different twist on a bad nerf.</span></td>
